.sh NAME
xclose \*- close a picture file
.sh SYNOPSIS
int
.bd xclose
(area)
.s3
int area[30]
.sh DESCRIPTION
.lp +9 9
area	work area for CXAP
.i0
.s3
.it Xclose
closes a picture file.
If the picture file associated with
.it area
was opened using
.it setupw,
the picture file is checked to insure its correctness.
If too few or too many rows were written to the picture file,
the header is changed to reflect this fact.
.i0
.s3
Function value is -1 on error, 0 on end-of-file and +1 on
success.
